{"type":"message","id":"8ad4d1f8","parentId":"d8ab940a","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:30:47.797Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Guillermo wants me to update my memory curation system to properly use PARA vault for demoted items. Let me design and implement this.\n\nThe fix involves:\n1. Update the nightly curation cron job prompt to include PARA demotion\n2. Document the updated flow\n3. Maybe update AGENTS.md with the new curation rules\n\nLet me think about what specifically needs to change:\n\n1. The nightly memory curation cron job needs updated instructions to demote trimmed items to vault/knowledge/\n2. MEMORY.md reference pointers should mention the PARA vault demotion\n3. The PARA-GUIDE.md could use a refresh\n\n\n4. Now I need to look at what the current curation cron job actually looks like to understand what I'm working with.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01A3aacop9xcNtPKHz4JKhB4","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"list"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":231,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":73448,"totalTokens":73682,"cost":{"input":0.000015000000000000002,"output":0.005775000000000001,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0.45905,"total":0.46484000000000003}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773880239208}}
{"type":"message","id":"5ab0d7c1","parentId":"8ad4d1f8","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:30:47.966Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01A3aacop9xcNtPKHz4JKhB4","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"jobs\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"251c316a-15df-4a45-91f8-22b33c810e95\",\n      \"name\": \"Todoist → MC Sync (30min)\",\n      \"description\": \"Sync Todoist tasks into Mission Control Dojo every 30 minutes\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772388194475,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773878417162,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"*/30 * * * *\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync.sh and output result\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773880200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773878400008,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 17154,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"runningAtMs\": 1773880200006\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"ad96575e-69a9-4a88-b806-7208bb019348\",\n      \"name\": \"Pre-Standup Prep (4:30 PM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772504193934,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773793855106,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"30 8 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the pre-standup prep script: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/standup_prep.py 2>&1 | tee /data/workspace/logs/standup-prep-run-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log. This runs at 4:30 PM HKT before the 5PM standup. It triages new Todoist tasks, pings squad agents for status, syncs MC completions to Todoist, scans ggv.molt inbox, and writes the prep state file for daily_standup.py to consume at 5PM. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773880200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773793813774,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 41332,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"runningAtMs\": 1773880210563\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"13b4eaa0-5069-419a-a3c0-ee7a39a995a7\",\n      \"name\": \"Todoist Inbox Triage (Hourly)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772505333253,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773878421067,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 * * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the Todoist inbox triage script: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/todoist_triage.py. This runs silently every hour. It fetches raw Todoist inbox tasks, rewrites titles to be specific + actionable, assigns project/owner/priority, and adds the 🦎 marker. No output to Guillermo — log only. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773882000000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773878417162,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 3905,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"e94b898e-e811-43e5-ac04-01d2c739d924\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:discord:channel:1468164160398557216\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Status Report (09:00 HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772413744739,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773795693816,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120,\n        \"message\": \"Generate Molty's daily status report and post to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216).\\n\\nStep 1 — Query MC for Molty's active tasks:\\nexec: curl -s 'https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/tasks?assignee=molty' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc' | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; tasks=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(t.get('status','?'), '|', t.get('title','?')[:50]) for t in tasks if t.get('status') not in ('done','blocked')]\\\"\\n\\nStep 2 — Get fleet version state:\\nexec: cat /data/workspace/state/openclaw-fleet-version.json 2>/dev/null\\n\\nStep 3 — Get latest backup info:\\nexec: ls -lht /data/workspace/backups/*.tar.gz 2>/dev/null | head -3\\n\\nStep 4 — Post this message to Discord channel 1468164160398557216 using the message tool:\\n\\n**Molty Daily Status — {DAY}, {DATE} (09:00 HKT)**\\n\\n**Active Tasks (MC)**\\n[List in_progress and assigned tasks from Step 1, grouped by status]\\n\\n**Fleet Versions**\\n[From Step 2 — molty/raphael/leonardo current versions]\\n\\n**Backup**\\n• Last: [most recent file from Step 3]\\n• Next: Daily at 21:00 HKT\\n\\n**Gateway:** local · reachable ✅\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773882000000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773795656921,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 36895,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 8,\n        \"lastDeliveryError\": \"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\",\n        \"lastError\": \"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"bdb28765-f508-4271-a04d-9408d39f49fd\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Standup 5PM HKT (Webchat)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770276918859,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773824466876,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Daily standup time (5PM HKT). Generate and send the standup review.\\n\\nStep 1 — Run Todoist↔MC sync:\\nexec: bash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1\\n\\nStep 2 — Get Todoist tasks:\\nexec: curl -s 'https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4' | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); tasks=data.get('results',data) if isinstance(data,dict) else data; [print(f'{t.get(\\\\\\\"due\\\\\\\",{}).get(\\\\\\\"date\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"no-date\\\\\\\")} | {t.get(\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\")}') for t in (tasks if isinstance(tasks,list) else [])]\\\"\\n\\nStep 3 — Get MC tasks for squad status:\\nexec: curl -s 'https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/tasks?status=in_progress' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc' | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; tasks=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(f'{t.get(\\\\\\\"assignees\\\\\\\",[\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"])[0]} | {t.get(\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\")}') for t in tasks[:10]]\\\"\\n\\nStep 4 — Format and send standup to WEBCHAT (Guillermo's preferred channel).\\n\\nFormat:\\n📋 **Daily Standup — {Day}, {Date}**\\n\\n**TODAY'S TASKS:**\\n1. ⬜ [task from Todoist due today]\\n2. ⬜ [task 2]\\n...\\n\\n**OVERDUE:**\\n⚠️ [any overdue tasks]\\n\\n**SQUAD:**\\n• Raphael: [in_progress task or 'clear']\\n• Leonardo: [in_progress task or 'clear']\\n\\n**TOMORROW'S FOCUS?**\\n→ What's the ONE thing?\\n\\n_Reply inline: '1 done, 2 drop' etc. Then state tomorrow's focus._\\n\\nSend this message to webchat. Do NOT generate a Notion page.\\n\\nStep 5 — Also send to Telegram (target 1097408992) as backup.\\n\\nReply STANDUP_SENT when complete.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773910800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773824400010,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 66866,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 1,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastError\": \"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\",\n        \"lastDeliveryError\": \"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"webchat\",\n        \"to\": \"1097408992:12609\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"d9da8767-0650-43f8-9c6b-420affb67c40\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Backup (9 PM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771075774802,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773838885481,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 13 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the daily backup:\\n\\n1. Run backup: bash /data/workspace/backups/backup.sh\\n2. Return result as plain text: backup size, success/fail.\\n\\nDo NOT run updates (handled by morning cron). Do NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773925200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773838800011,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 85470,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"c0705ffd-9c7f-4f90-839b-7f3a9d660371\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Fleet Update Check (21:15 HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771119666523,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773839715247,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"15 21 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check if a new OpenClaw version is available.\\n\\nStep 1 — Check current vs latest:\\nexec: openclaw update status 2>&1\\n\\nStep 2 — If update available:\\na) Fetch the tweet from @openclaw about this release (use fxtwitter API)\\nb) Fetch GitHub release notes: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/releases/tag/v{VERSION}\\nc) Create a summary following the format in memory/refs/notification-formats.md under 'OpenClaw Update Summary'\\nd) Send to Telegram (target 1097408992) with:\\n   - Table: Feature | What It Does | How We Use It\\n   - 'Most Relevant for Us' section (top 3)\\n   - End with: Reply /update to install\\n\\nStep 3 — If already on latest: reply HEARTBEAT_OK (no message to Guillermo)\\n\\nStep 4 — Update /data/workspace/state/openclaw-fleet-version.json with last_notified_version so we don't spam.\\n\\nRULES:\\n- Only notify ONCE per new version\\n- Focus on TMNT-relevant features\\n- Skip irrelevant providers (BlueBubbles, Mattermost, etc.)\\n- Call out fixes for issues we've hit\\n- Never auto-update without approval\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164181155909743\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773926100000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773839700012,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 15235,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"b2d4e6ce-7826-4cd7-b173-2272d7bea43a\",\n      \"name\": \"Nightly Memory Curation (11PM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 23 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"agentId\": \"\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"message\": \"Nightly memory curation — 23:00 HKT. You are in an isolated session.\\n\\nStep 1 — Read today's daily log and MEMORY.md:\\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'No daily log yet'\\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\\n\\nStep 2 — Identify gaps: decisions made today not in MEMORY.md, tasks completed not recorded, lessons learned not captured, infra changes undocumented.\\n\\nStep 3 — Patch gaps: append any missing durable items to /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md. If MEMORY.md needs updating (new lessons, key decisions), edit it — but keep it under 15KB.\\n\\nStep 4 — Check MEMORY.md size:\\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\\nIf over 15000 bytes, trim the lowest-value entries (old completed-plan notes, historical status entries) to get back under cap.\\n\\nStep 5 — Commit:\\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add memory/ MEMORY.md && git commit -m 'memory: nightly curation ${TODAY}' 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\\n\\nStep 6 — Post summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) using the message tool:\\nFormat:\\n**🧠 Nightly Memory Curation — {DATE}**\\n\\n[N gaps found and patched / or: No gaps found — memory current]\\n\\n**Added:**\\n- [item 1]\\n- [item 2]\\n(or: Nothing to add)\\n\\n**MEMORY.md:** [size]KB [under/over cap]\\n\\nDo NOT post if nothing changed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK instead.\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773932400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773846000009,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 92159,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773846092168,\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"65be2a8d-8d53-405d-8e2e-b7f9da6fb4b6\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:discord:channel:1468164181155909743\",\n      \"name\": \"Fleet Health Check (Pre-Overnight)\",\n      \"description\": \"Checks Raphael, Leonardo, April gateway health 30 min before overnight windows. Auto-redeploys or alerts if down.\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1773397751966,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773849643150,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 16 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run fleet health check for all overnight agents:\\n\\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/fleet-health-monitor.py all 2>&1\\n\\nIf all healthy, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\nIf any agent is down and auto-redeploy worked, confirm the recovery.\\nIf any agent is down and auto-redeploy failed, the script already posted an alert — just confirm you saw it.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773936000000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773849622872,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 20278,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"bee2b3f1-f58d-4641-9dd6-4d76336909c8\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"sessionKey\": \"agent:main:cron:80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa\",\n      \"name\": \"PLAN-017a: MC Stale Task Escalation\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1773770658791,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773853266838,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 1 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the MC stale task escalation check.\\n\\n1. Run: python3 /data/workspace/scripts/mc-stale-escalation.py\\n2. Read the output file at /data/workspace/logs/stale-escalation-discord-{TODAY}.txt (replace {TODAY} with today's date YYYY-MM-DD)\\n3. If the file exists and has content, parse the JSON and post the 'message' field to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216)\\n4. If no stale tasks (file shows no escalations), skip the Discord post silently\\n5. Log result\\n\\nToday's date format: use $(date +%Y-%m-%d) to get it. This is a fully automated check — no confirmation needed.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773939600000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773853238061,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 28777,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa\",\n      \"name\": \"Molty Nightly Task Worker\",\n      \"description\": \"Executes Molty-owned Todoist tasks autonomously. Results logged for morning briefing.\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771928556133,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773857435898,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 18 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Nightly task worker — 03:00 HKT. You are running in an isolated session with no prior conversation context. Follow Phase 0 before touching anything.\\n\\n## PHASE 0: PRE-FLIGHT (MANDATORY)\\n\\nStep 1 — Read memory logs:\\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && YESTERDAY=$(date -d 'yesterday' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-1d +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null && cat /data/workspace/memory/${YESTERDAY}.md 2>/dev/null\\n\\nStep 2 — Get open Todoist tasks (🦎 Molty personal tasks only):\\nexec: curl -s 'https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4' | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); tasks=data.get('results',data) if isinstance(data,dict) else data; [print(f'[{t[\\\\\\\"id\\\\\\\"]}] {t.get(\\\\\\\"content\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\")}') for t in (tasks if isinstance(tasks,list) else []) if '🦎' in t.get('content','')]\\\"\\n\\nStep 3 — Query Paperclip for Molty's open issues (PRIMARY task source):\\n```\\nPCP_TOKEN=pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\\nPCP_URL=https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app\\nPCP_AGENT=0e4e3ca3-0cc0-4370-83ea-2e82fbf3ee1d\\nfor COMPANY in '4d845c5e-5c36-4fc5-827d-5a577e683cdb:TMNT' 'bd625bc3-1268-4b0f-a591-06bf06ca8d27:Brinc' '722bc707-271b-43be-a073-059270e031d2:Cerebro'; do\\n  CID=$(echo $COMPANY | cut -d: -f1); CNAME=$(echo $COMPANY | cut -d: -f2)\\n  echo \\\"=== $CNAME ===\\\"\\n  curl -s -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer $PCP_TOKEN\\\" \\\"$PCP_URL/api/companies/$CID/issues?assigneeAgentId=$PCP_AGENT\\\" | python3 -c \\\"import json,sys; [print(f'[{i[\\\\\\\"identifier\\\\\\\"]}] [{i[\\\\\\\"status\\\\\\\"]}] [{i[\\\\\\\"priority\\\\\\\"]}] {i[\\\\\\\"title\\\\\\\"]}') for i in json.load(sys.stdin) if i.get('status') not in ('done','cancelled')]\\\"\\ndone\\n```\\nexec the above script.\\n\\nStep 4 — Cross-reference. Skip if: appears in memory log as done/in_progress today, OR in overnight log from today.\\n\\nStep 5 — Write pre-flight summary to /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md before proceeding.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PHASE 1: TASK CLASSIFICATION\\nAUTO: research/write/draft/plan/compile/summarise/code → execute\\nFLAG: needs Guillermo decision / external send / financial / ambiguous → write to 🚧 Blocked\\nTime budget: target 90 min, hard stop 2h.\\n\\nPaperclip issue priorities:\\n- critical/high → execute first\\n- medium → execute if time allows\\n- low/p3 → skip if budget tight\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PHASE 2: EXECUTION\\nFor each AUTO task:\\n1. Execute fully\\n2. After completion:\\n   - POST completion comment to Paperclip issue:\\n     curl -s -X POST -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\\\" -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"body\\\":\\\"Completed in overnight run. [summary]\\\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/issues/{ISSUE_ID}/comments\\n   - PATCH issue status to done:\\n     curl -s -X PATCH -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\\\" -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"status\\\":\\\"done\\\",\\\"comment\\\":\\\"[what changed and why]\\\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/issues/{ISSUE_ID}\\n   - Close matching Todoist task if originated there\\n   - Write to overnight log\\n3. If attempted but failed → log as ❌ Failed with exact reason\\n4. If not attempted (out of budget / requires human) → log as ⏭ Skipped with reason\\n\\n---\\n\\n## PHASE 3: REPORT (MANDATORY — write log EVEN IF nothing was done)\\n\\nStep 3a — Write Molty's shared overnight log:\\nexec: mkdir -p /data/shared/logs\\n\\nWrite to /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-${TODAY}.md using this EXACT format (all 5 sections required — write \\\"(none)\\\" if empty):\\n\\n# Overnight — Molty — {DATE}\\n\\n## ✅ Completed\\n- **{task name}** [{identifier}] → {brief result, commit/link/file if applicable}\\n\\n## 👀 Under Review\\n- **{task name}** → needs: {what Guillermo needs to decide/review} | link: {url or path}\\n\\n## ❌ Failed\\n- **{task name}** → why: {exact reason — error message, API failure, missing data}\\n\\n## 🚧 Blocked\\n- **{task name}** → need from Guillermo: {specific ask — a key, a decision, a file, a name}\\n\\n## ⏭ Skipped\\n- **{task name}** → reason: {already done per log | out of time budget | requires human | ambiguous}\\n\\nRULES:\\n- Every section must be present. Write \\\"(none)\\\" if empty — never omit a section.\\n- ❌ Failed MUST say why (not just \\\"failed\\\").\\n- 🚧 Blocked MUST say exactly what Guillermo needs to provide.\\n- 👀 Under Review MUST include a link or file path.\\n- ✅ Completed MUST be attempted in Paperclip status update + closed in Todoist if applicable.\\n\\nStep 3b — Consolidate all three agent logs and post to #squad-updates:\\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null && echo '---' && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-raphael-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'Raphael log not available' && echo '---' && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-leonardo-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'Leonardo log not available'\\n\\nPost ONE consolidated message to Discord #squad-updates (channel 1468164181155909743) in this format:\\n🌙 **Squad Overnight Report — {DATE}**\\n\\n🦎 **Molty**\\n[completed/under-review/failed/blocked summary — 3 lines max per agent]\\n\\n🔴 **Raphael**\\n[summary or 'Log not available']\\n\\n🔵 **Leonardo**\\n[summary or 'Log not available']\\n\\nIf a log is missing, note it but still post.\\n\\nStep 3c — Commit logs:\\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add logs/ && git commit -m \\\"log: overnight tasks ${TODAY}\\\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\\n\\nStep 3d — POST to Paperclip TMNT company activity feed:\\ncurl -s -X POST -H \\\"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\\\" -H \\\"Content-Type: application/json\\\" -d '{\\\"body\\\":\\\"Overnight run complete — {DATE}. See /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-{DATE}.md for full report.\\\",\\\"agentId\\\":\\\"0e4e3ca3-0cc0-4370-83ea-2e82fbf3ee1d\\\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/companies/4d845c5e-5c36-4fc5-827d-5a577e683cdb/feed 2>/dev/null || true\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 1500\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164181155909743\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773943200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773856800014,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 514559,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      },\n      \"agentId\": \"main\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"8991c017-037d-4fa2-863c-f3b2700aa9cc\",\n      \"name\": \"Overnight Sync — Paperclip → Todoist (04:00 HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772505589348,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773864028657,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 20 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"UTC\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the overnight sync (Paperclip → Todoist + Notion): /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/overnight_sync.py 2>&1. Syncs Paperclip issues marked done overnight → closes matching Todoist tasks + updates Notion standup rows. Silent — logs only. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773950400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773864018425,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 10232,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"7906d2f7-ef74-481a-8aff-53ea44d32eee\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"memory-size-guardrail\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770798635243,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773867617612,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 5 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Run: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\\n\\nCaps: MEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each.\\n\\nIf ANY file exceeds its cap, return a summary with file name, current size, and cap.\\n\\nAlso: move any memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files older than 7 days to memory/archive/.\\n\\nIf everything is under cap, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\\n\\nDo NOT call the message tool. Return your summary as plain text only; the delivery system will post it.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120,\n        \"text\": \"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Review: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\\n\\nMEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each. No action needed unless a file is close to its cap.\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773954000000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773867600008,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 17604,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"8b748f23-91d0-425d-9e4b-e7246e46ce8c\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Daily Morning Briefing (6AM HKT)\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770354555841,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773873018664,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"30 6 * * *\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run the morning briefing script and send output to Guillermo on Telegram.\\n\\nStep 1 — Run the script:\\nexec: python3 /data/workspace/scripts/morning-briefing.py 2>&1\\n\\nStep 2 — Send the EXACT output (no changes, no embellishments) to Telegram (target 1097408992). Use the message tool.\\n\\nStep 3 — Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when done.\\n\\nCRITICAL: Send the script output EXACTLY as-is. Do not add weather if the script already has it. Do not add sections. Do not reformat. Script output = message content.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773959400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773873000006,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 18658,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": false\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"none\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"b6b54820-3a9b-4904-a2c8-1cdffc72dd6a\",\n      \"name\": \"Weekly MC Digest (Fri 17:00 HKT)\",\n      \"description\": \"Weekly fleet digest: tasks completed, velocity, cost breakdown. Posts to #command-center + Telegram\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772388199969,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773378619119,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 * * 5\",\n        \"staggerMs\": 0\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run /data/workspace/scripts/mc-weekly-digest.sh and post the output to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216)\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773968400000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773378610712,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastStatus\": \"error\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 8407,\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\",\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 2,\n        \"lastError\": \"Discord recipient is required. Use \\\"channel:<id>\\\" for channels or \\\"user:<id>\\\" for DMs.\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"44fb9d22-a77a-4de1-9c09-5edef483264e\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"weekly-para-curation\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770180106367,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773594009749,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 1 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"🗂️ WEEKLY PARA CURATION\\n\\nExecute the PARA curation script:\\n\\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/para_curation.py 2>&1\\n\\nScript will:\\n1. Scan shared project directories\\n2. Archive files older than 1 year\\n3. Log migration details\\n4. Create a migration report\\n\\nCheck /data/workspace/logs/para_curation.log for details.\\n\\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774198800000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773594000012,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 9737,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"f17da2d2-3b49-4be5-be9d-d29a27a8dbb9\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"healthcheck:security-audit\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1770299752473,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773601254716,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 3 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"next-heartbeat\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Run a security audit: execute `openclaw security audit --deep` and `openclaw update status`. Compare results against the last audit. If any NEW findings appear (not previously accepted risks), return them clearly. Save results to memory/security-audit-latest.md. Accepted risks: dangerouslyDisableDeviceAuth=true, Sonnet 4 weak tier warning, Discord allowlist warning.\\n\\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only. The delivery system handles routing.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 180\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774206000000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773601200028,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 54688,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"delivered\",\n        \"lastDelivered\": true\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"discord\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"3db9477e-5dee-4731-bfb4-9e0abfcbcab2\",\n      \"agentId\": \"main\",\n      \"name\": \"Weekly Memory Health Check\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1771334751465,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1773626420619,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 10 * * 1\",\n        \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"## Weekly Memory Health Check\\n\\nRun these checks and report findings:\\n\\n1. **Index Status**\\n   - Run `openclaw memory status` and capture: files indexed, chunks, embeddings cached\\n   - If files=0 but embeddings>0: INDEX IS CORRUPTED — run `openclaw memory index --force` to auto-fix, then re-check status\\n\\n2. **Canary Search Tests**\\n   - Search for \\\"Guillermo\\\" — should return results\\n   - Search for \\\"TMNT fleet\\\" — should return results\\n   - If both return 0: search is broken\\n\\n3. **Disk Usage**\\n   - Check /data/workspace/memory/ size\\n   - Check /data/.openclaw/memory/ size\\n\\n4. **QMD Status**\\n   - Check if any .qmd files exist (should be removed per Feb 23 decision)\\n\\nReport format:\\n- Summary status (PASS/FAIL)\\n- Severity (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH)\\n- Any auto-fixes applied\\n- Action items if manual intervention needed\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n        \"timeoutSeconds\": 120\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"to\": \"channel:1468164160398557216\",\n        \"bestEffort\": true\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1774231200000,\n        \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773626400013,\n        \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDurationMs\": 20606,\n        \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n        \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n        \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"unknown\"\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"9af41e20-e097-474a-ba80-9bb822e4c64d\",\n      \"name\": \"Monthly Core Files Review\",\n      \"description\": \"1st of each month: Review SOUL.md/IDENTITY.md accuracy, check MEMORY.md size, update mistake-tracker recurrence counts.\",\n      \"enabled\": true,\n      \"createdAtMs\": 1772613275378,\n      \"updatedAtMs\": 1772613275378,\n      \"schedule\": {\n        \"kind\": \"cron\",\n        \"expr\": \"0 9 1 * *\"\n      },\n      \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n      \"wakeMode\": \"now\",\n      \"payload\": {\n        \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n        \"message\": \"Monthly core files review (1st of month, 09:00 HKT).\\n\\nTasks:\\n1. Check MEMORY.md size with wc -c. Must be <5KB. If over, cull immediately.\\n2. Review SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md for accuracy.\\n3. Check memory/refs/mistake-tracker.md for any recurrences >0.\\n4. Post summary to Telegram.\\n\\nIf all good: MONTHLY_REVIEW_OK\\nIf action needed: take it and report.\",\n        \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\"\n      },\n      \"delivery\": {\n        \"mode\": \"announce\",\n        \"channel\": \"last\"\n      },\n      \"state\": {\n        \"nextRunAtMs\": 1775005200000\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"total\": 19,\n  \"offset\": 0,\n  \"limit\": 19,\n  \"hasMore\": false,\n  \"nextOffset\": null\n}"}],"details":{"jobs":[{"id":"251c316a-15df-4a45-91f8-22b33c810e95","name":"Todoist → MC Sync (30min)","description":"Sync Todoist tasks into Mission Control Dojo every 30 minutes","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772388194475,"updatedAtMs":1773878417162,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"*/30 * * * *"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync.sh and output result","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773880200000,"lastRunAtMs":1773878400008,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":17154,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false,"runningAtMs":1773880200006}},{"id":"ad96575e-69a9-4a88-b806-7208bb019348","name":"Pre-Standup Prep (4:30 PM HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772504193934,"updatedAtMs":1773793855106,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"30 8 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the pre-standup prep script: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/standup_prep.py 2>&1 | tee /data/workspace/logs/standup-prep-run-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log. This runs at 4:30 PM HKT before the 5PM standup. It triages new Todoist tasks, pings squad agents for status, syncs MC completions to Todoist, scans ggv.molt inbox, and writes the prep state file for daily_standup.py to consume at 5PM. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":900},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773880200000,"lastRunAtMs":1773793813774,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":41332,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false,"runningAtMs":1773880210563}},{"id":"13b4eaa0-5069-419a-a3c0-ee7a39a995a7","name":"Todoist Inbox Triage (Hourly)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772505333253,"updatedAtMs":1773878421067,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 * * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the Todoist inbox triage script: /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/todoist_triage.py. This runs silently every hour. It fetches raw Todoist inbox tasks, rewrites titles to be specific + actionable, assigns project/owner/priority, and adds the 🦎 marker. No output to Guillermo — log only. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773882000000,"lastRunAtMs":1773878417162,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":3905,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false}},{"id":"e94b898e-e811-43e5-ac04-01d2c739d924","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:discord:channel:1468164160398557216","name":"Daily Status Report (09:00 HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772413744739,"updatedAtMs":1773795693816,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120,"message":"Generate Molty's daily status report and post to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216).\n\nStep 1 — Query MC for Molty's active tasks:\nexec: curl -s 'https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/tasks?assignee=molty' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc' | python3 -c \"import json,sys; tasks=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(t.get('status','?'), '|', t.get('title','?')[:50]) for t in tasks if t.get('status') not in ('done','blocked')]\"\n\nStep 2 — Get fleet version state:\nexec: cat /data/workspace/state/openclaw-fleet-version.json 2>/dev/null\n\nStep 3 — Get latest backup info:\nexec: ls -lht /data/workspace/backups/*.tar.gz 2>/dev/null | head -3\n\nStep 4 — Post this message to Discord channel 1468164160398557216 using the message tool:\n\n**Molty Daily Status — {DAY}, {DATE} (09:00 HKT)**\n\n**Active Tasks (MC)**\n[List in_progress and assigned tasks from Step 1, grouped by status]\n\n**Fleet Versions**\n[From Step 2 — molty/raphael/leonardo current versions]\n\n**Backup**\n• Last: [most recent file from Step 3]\n• Next: Daily at 21:00 HKT\n\n**Gateway:** local · reachable ✅"},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773882000000,"lastRunAtMs":1773795656921,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":36895,"lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":8,"lastDeliveryError":"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed","lastError":"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed"}},{"id":"bdb28765-f508-4271-a04d-9408d39f49fd","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Standup 5PM HKT (Webchat)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770276918859,"updatedAtMs":1773824466876,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Daily standup time (5PM HKT). Generate and send the standup review.\n\nStep 1 — Run Todoist↔MC sync:\nexec: bash /data/workspace/scripts/mc-todoist-sync-v2.sh 2>&1\n\nStep 2 — Get Todoist tasks:\nexec: curl -s 'https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4' | python3 -c \"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); tasks=data.get('results',data) if isinstance(data,dict) else data; [print(f'{t.get(\\\"due\\\",{}).get(\\\"date\\\",\\\"no-date\\\")} | {t.get(\\\"content\\\",\\\"\\\")}') for t in (tasks if isinstance(tasks,list) else [])]\"\n\nStep 3 — Get MC tasks for squad status:\nexec: curl -s 'https://resilient-chinchilla-241.convex.site/api/tasks?status=in_progress' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 232e4ddf7d69c31e01ad0fa0a61f70c29e4837ed018a153cce1a429842bb7cbc' | python3 -c \"import json,sys; tasks=json.load(sys.stdin); [print(f'{t.get(\\\"assignees\\\",[\\\"\\\"])[0]} | {t.get(\\\"title\\\",\\\"\\\")}') for t in tasks[:10]]\"\n\nStep 4 — Format and send standup to WEBCHAT (Guillermo's preferred channel).\n\nFormat:\n📋 **Daily Standup — {Day}, {Date}**\n\n**TODAY'S TASKS:**\n1. ⬜ [task from Todoist due today]\n2. ⬜ [task 2]\n...\n\n**OVERDUE:**\n⚠️ [any overdue tasks]\n\n**SQUAD:**\n• Raphael: [in_progress task or 'clear']\n• Leonardo: [in_progress task or 'clear']\n\n**TOMORROW'S FOCUS?**\n→ What's the ONE thing?\n\n_Reply inline: '1 done, 2 drop' etc. Then state tomorrow's focus._\n\nSend this message to webchat. Do NOT generate a Notion page.\n\nStep 5 — Also send to Telegram (target 1097408992) as backup.\n\nReply STANDUP_SENT when complete.","model":"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773910800000,"lastRunAtMs":1773824400010,"lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":66866,"consecutiveErrors":1,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","lastDelivered":false,"lastError":"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed","lastDeliveryError":"⚠️ ✉️ Message failed"},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"webchat","to":"1097408992:12609"}},{"id":"d9da8767-0650-43f8-9c6b-420affb67c40","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Backup (9 PM HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771075774802,"updatedAtMs":1773838885481,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 13 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the daily backup:\n\n1. Run backup: bash /data/workspace/backups/backup.sh\n2. Return result as plain text: backup size, success/fail.\n\nDo NOT run updates (handled by morning cron). Do NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773925200000,"lastRunAtMs":1773838800011,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":85470,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":true,"lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered"}},{"id":"c0705ffd-9c7f-4f90-839b-7f3a9d660371","agentId":"main","name":"Fleet Update Check (21:15 HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771119666523,"updatedAtMs":1773839715247,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"15 21 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Check if a new OpenClaw version is available.\n\nStep 1 — Check current vs latest:\nexec: openclaw update status 2>&1\n\nStep 2 — If update available:\na) Fetch the tweet from @openclaw about this release (use fxtwitter API)\nb) Fetch GitHub release notes: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/releases/tag/v{VERSION}\nc) Create a summary following the format in memory/refs/notification-formats.md under 'OpenClaw Update Summary'\nd) Send to Telegram (target 1097408992) with:\n   - Table: Feature | What It Does | How We Use It\n   - 'Most Relevant for Us' section (top 3)\n   - End with: Reply /update to install\n\nStep 3 — If already on latest: reply HEARTBEAT_OK (no message to Guillermo)\n\nStep 4 — Update /data/workspace/state/openclaw-fleet-version.json with last_notified_version so we don't spam.\n\nRULES:\n- Only notify ONCE per new version\n- Focus on TMNT-relevant features\n- Skip irrelevant providers (BlueBubbles, Mattermost, etc.)\n- Call out fixes for issues we've hit\n- Never auto-update without approval","model":"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-5","timeoutSeconds":300},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164181155909743"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773926100000,"lastRunAtMs":1773839700012,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":15235,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered"}},{"id":"b2d4e6ce-7826-4cd7-b173-2272d7bea43a","name":"Nightly Memory Curation (11PM HKT)","enabled":true,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 23 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","agentId":"","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","message":"Nightly memory curation — 23:00 HKT. You are in an isolated session.\n\nStep 1 — Read today's daily log and MEMORY.md:\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'No daily log yet'\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\n\nStep 2 — Identify gaps: decisions made today not in MEMORY.md, tasks completed not recorded, lessons learned not captured, infra changes undocumented.\n\nStep 3 — Patch gaps: append any missing durable items to /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md. If MEMORY.md needs updating (new lessons, key decisions), edit it — but keep it under 15KB.\n\nStep 4 — Check MEMORY.md size:\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\nIf over 15000 bytes, trim the lowest-value entries (old completed-plan notes, historical status entries) to get back under cap.\n\nStep 5 — Commit:\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add memory/ MEMORY.md && git commit -m 'memory: nightly curation ${TODAY}' 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\n\nStep 6 — Post summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) using the message tool:\nFormat:\n**🧠 Nightly Memory Curation — {DATE}**\n\n[N gaps found and patched / or: No gaps found — memory current]\n\n**Added:**\n- [item 1]\n- [item 2]\n(or: Nothing to add)\n\n**MEMORY.md:** [size]KB [under/over cap]\n\nDo NOT post if nothing changed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK instead.","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773932400000,"lastRunAtMs":1773846000009,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":92159,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"updatedAtMs":1773846092168,"wakeMode":"now"},{"id":"65be2a8d-8d53-405d-8e2e-b7f9da6fb4b6","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:discord:channel:1468164181155909743","name":"Fleet Health Check (Pre-Overnight)","description":"Checks Raphael, Leonardo, April gateway health 30 min before overnight windows. Auto-redeploys or alerts if down.","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1773397751966,"updatedAtMs":1773849643150,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 16 * * *","tz":"UTC"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run fleet health check for all overnight agents:\n\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/fleet-health-monitor.py all 2>&1\n\nIf all healthy, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\nIf any agent is down and auto-redeploy worked, confirm the recovery.\nIf any agent is down and auto-redeploy failed, the script already posted an alert — just confirm you saw it.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773936000000,"lastRunAtMs":1773849622872,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":20278,"lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}},{"id":"bee2b3f1-f58d-4641-9dd6-4d76336909c8","agentId":"main","sessionKey":"agent:main:cron:80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa","name":"PLAN-017a: MC Stale Task Escalation","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1773770658791,"updatedAtMs":1773853266838,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 1 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the MC stale task escalation check.\n\n1. Run: python3 /data/workspace/scripts/mc-stale-escalation.py\n2. Read the output file at /data/workspace/logs/stale-escalation-discord-{TODAY}.txt (replace {TODAY} with today's date YYYY-MM-DD)\n3. If the file exists and has content, parse the JSON and post the 'message' field to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216)\n4. If no stale tasks (file shows no escalations), skip the Discord post silently\n5. Log result\n\nToday's date format: use $(date +%Y-%m-%d) to get it. This is a fully automated check — no confirmation needed.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773939600000,"lastRunAtMs":1773853238061,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":28777,"lastDelivered":false,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0}},{"id":"80105aa4-e6de-4cbb-ae8a-d9e75c84b3fa","name":"Molty Nightly Task Worker","description":"Executes Molty-owned Todoist tasks autonomously. Results logged for morning briefing.","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771928556133,"updatedAtMs":1773857435898,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 18 * * *","tz":"UTC","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Nightly task worker — 03:00 HKT. You are running in an isolated session with no prior conversation context. Follow Phase 0 before touching anything.\n\n## PHASE 0: PRE-FLIGHT (MANDATORY)\n\nStep 1 — Read memory logs:\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && YESTERDAY=$(date -d 'yesterday' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-1d +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null && cat /data/workspace/memory/${YESTERDAY}.md 2>/dev/null\n\nStep 2 — Get open Todoist tasks (🦎 Molty personal tasks only):\nexec: curl -s 'https://api.todoist.com/api/v1/tasks' -H 'Authorization: Bearer 9a26743814658c9e82d92aa716b46a9b0a2257c4' | python3 -c \"import json,sys; data=json.load(sys.stdin); tasks=data.get('results',data) if isinstance(data,dict) else data; [print(f'[{t[\\\"id\\\"]}] {t.get(\\\"content\\\",\\\"\\\")}') for t in (tasks if isinstance(tasks,list) else []) if '🦎' in t.get('content','')]\"\n\nStep 3 — Query Paperclip for Molty's open issues (PRIMARY task source):\n```\nPCP_TOKEN=pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\nPCP_URL=https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app\nPCP_AGENT=0e4e3ca3-0cc0-4370-83ea-2e82fbf3ee1d\nfor COMPANY in '4d845c5e-5c36-4fc5-827d-5a577e683cdb:TMNT' 'bd625bc3-1268-4b0f-a591-06bf06ca8d27:Brinc' '722bc707-271b-43be-a073-059270e031d2:Cerebro'; do\n  CID=$(echo $COMPANY | cut -d: -f1); CNAME=$(echo $COMPANY | cut -d: -f2)\n  echo \"=== $CNAME ===\"\n  curl -s -H \"Authorization: Bearer $PCP_TOKEN\" \"$PCP_URL/api/companies/$CID/issues?assigneeAgentId=$PCP_AGENT\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; [print(f'[{i[\\\"identifier\\\"]}] [{i[\\\"status\\\"]}] [{i[\\\"priority\\\"]}] {i[\\\"title\\\"]}') for i in json.load(sys.stdin) if i.get('status') not in ('done','cancelled')]\"\ndone\n```\nexec the above script.\n\nStep 4 — Cross-reference. Skip if: appears in memory log as done/in_progress today, OR in overnight log from today.\n\nStep 5 — Write pre-flight summary to /data/workspace/logs/overnight-tasks-${TODAY}.md before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n## PHASE 1: TASK CLASSIFICATION\nAUTO: research/write/draft/plan/compile/summarise/code → execute\nFLAG: needs Guillermo decision / external send / financial / ambiguous → write to 🚧 Blocked\nTime budget: target 90 min, hard stop 2h.\n\nPaperclip issue priorities:\n- critical/high → execute first\n- medium → execute if time allows\n- low/p3 → skip if budget tight\n\n---\n\n## PHASE 2: EXECUTION\nFor each AUTO task:\n1. Execute fully\n2. After completion:\n   - POST completion comment to Paperclip issue:\n     curl -s -X POST -H \"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"body\":\"Completed in overnight run. [summary]\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/issues/{ISSUE_ID}/comments\n   - PATCH issue status to done:\n     curl -s -X PATCH -H \"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"status\":\"done\",\"comment\":\"[what changed and why]\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/issues/{ISSUE_ID}\n   - Close matching Todoist task if originated there\n   - Write to overnight log\n3. If attempted but failed → log as ❌ Failed with exact reason\n4. If not attempted (out of budget / requires human) → log as ⏭ Skipped with reason\n\n---\n\n## PHASE 3: REPORT (MANDATORY — write log EVEN IF nothing was done)\n\nStep 3a — Write Molty's shared overnight log:\nexec: mkdir -p /data/shared/logs\n\nWrite to /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-${TODAY}.md using this EXACT format (all 5 sections required — write \"(none)\" if empty):\n\n# Overnight — Molty — {DATE}\n\n## ✅ Completed\n- **{task name}** [{identifier}] → {brief result, commit/link/file if applicable}\n\n## 👀 Under Review\n- **{task name}** → needs: {what Guillermo needs to decide/review} | link: {url or path}\n\n## ❌ Failed\n- **{task name}** → why: {exact reason — error message, API failure, missing data}\n\n## 🚧 Blocked\n- **{task name}** → need from Guillermo: {specific ask — a key, a decision, a file, a name}\n\n## ⏭ Skipped\n- **{task name}** → reason: {already done per log | out of time budget | requires human | ambiguous}\n\nRULES:\n- Every section must be present. Write \"(none)\" if empty — never omit a section.\n- ❌ Failed MUST say why (not just \"failed\").\n- 🚧 Blocked MUST say exactly what Guillermo needs to provide.\n- 👀 Under Review MUST include a link or file path.\n- ✅ Completed MUST be attempted in Paperclip status update + closed in Todoist if applicable.\n\nStep 3b — Consolidate all three agent logs and post to #squad-updates:\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null && echo '---' && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-raphael-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'Raphael log not available' && echo '---' && cat /data/shared/logs/overnight-leonardo-${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'Leonardo log not available'\n\nPost ONE consolidated message to Discord #squad-updates (channel 1468164181155909743) in this format:\n🌙 **Squad Overnight Report — {DATE}**\n\n🦎 **Molty**\n[completed/under-review/failed/blocked summary — 3 lines max per agent]\n\n🔴 **Raphael**\n[summary or 'Log not available']\n\n🔵 **Leonardo**\n[summary or 'Log not available']\n\nIf a log is missing, note it but still post.\n\nStep 3c — Commit logs:\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add logs/ && git commit -m \"log: overnight tasks ${TODAY}\" 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\n\nStep 3d — POST to Paperclip TMNT company activity feed:\ncurl -s -X POST -H \"Authorization: Bearer pcp_5c66968515127b7b30f95a688a8477955f197666c7cfafbe\" -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" -d '{\"body\":\"Overnight run complete — {DATE}. See /data/shared/logs/overnight-molty-{DATE}.md for full report.\",\"agentId\":\"0e4e3ca3-0cc0-4370-83ea-2e82fbf3ee1d\"}' https://paperclip-production-83f5.up.railway.app/api/companies/4d845c5e-5c36-4fc5-827d-5a577e683cdb/feed 2>/dev/null || true","model":"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6","timeoutSeconds":1500},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164181155909743"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773943200000,"lastRunAtMs":1773856800014,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":514559,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","lastDelivered":true},"agentId":"main"},{"id":"8991c017-037d-4fa2-863c-f3b2700aa9cc","name":"Overnight Sync — Paperclip → Todoist (04:00 HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772505589348,"updatedAtMs":1773864028657,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 20 * * *","tz":"UTC","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the overnight sync (Paperclip → Todoist + Notion): /data/workspace/.venv/bin/python3 /data/workspace/scripts/overnight_sync.py 2>&1. Syncs Paperclip issues marked done overnight → closes matching Todoist tasks + updates Notion standup rows. Silent — logs only. Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when complete.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"none","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773950400000,"lastRunAtMs":1773864018425,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":10232,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false}},{"id":"7906d2f7-ef74-481a-8aff-53ea44d32eee","agentId":"main","name":"memory-size-guardrail","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770798635243,"updatedAtMs":1773867617612,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 5 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Run: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\n\nCaps: MEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each.\n\nIf ANY file exceeds its cap, return a summary with file name, current size, and cap.\n\nAlso: move any memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md files older than 7 days to memory/archive/.\n\nIf everything is under cap, reply HEARTBEAT_OK.\n\nDo NOT call the message tool. Return your summary as plain text only; the delivery system will post it.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120,"text":"Check workspace file sizes for context bloat. Review: wc -c /data/workspace/*.md /data/workspace/memory/*.md 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -15\n\nMEMORY.md ≤15KB, AGENTS.md ≤8KB, TOOLS.md ≤5KB, daily files ≤10KB each. No action needed unless a file is close to its cap."},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773954000000,"lastRunAtMs":1773867600008,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":17604,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","lastDelivered":true}},{"id":"8b748f23-91d0-425d-9e4b-e7246e46ce8c","agentId":"main","name":"Daily Morning Briefing (6AM HKT)","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770354555841,"updatedAtMs":1773873018664,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"30 6 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run the morning briefing script and send output to Guillermo on Telegram.\n\nStep 1 — Run the script:\nexec: python3 /data/workspace/scripts/morning-briefing.py 2>&1\n\nStep 2 — Send the EXACT output (no changes, no embellishments) to Telegram (target 1097408992). Use the message tool.\n\nStep 3 — Reply HEARTBEAT_OK when done.\n\nCRITICAL: Send the script output EXACTLY as-is. Do not add weather if the script already has it. Do not add sections. Do not reformat. Script output = message content.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773959400000,"lastRunAtMs":1773873000006,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":18658,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","lastDelivered":false},"delivery":{"mode":"none"}},{"id":"b6b54820-3a9b-4904-a2c8-1cdffc72dd6a","name":"Weekly MC Digest (Fri 17:00 HKT)","description":"Weekly fleet digest: tasks completed, velocity, cost breakdown. Posts to #command-center + Telegram","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772388199969,"updatedAtMs":1773378619119,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 * * 5","staggerMs":0},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run /data/workspace/scripts/mc-weekly-digest.sh and post the output to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216)","timeoutSeconds":180},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773968400000,"lastRunAtMs":1773378610712,"lastRunStatus":"error","lastStatus":"error","lastDurationMs":8407,"lastDeliveryStatus":"unknown","consecutiveErrors":2,"lastError":"Discord recipient is required. Use \"channel:<id>\" for channels or \"user:<id>\" for DMs."}},{"id":"44fb9d22-a77a-4de1-9c09-5edef483264e","agentId":"main","name":"weekly-para-curation","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770180106367,"updatedAtMs":1773594009749,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 1 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"🗂️ WEEKLY PARA CURATION\n\nExecute the PARA curation script:\n\npython3 /data/workspace/scripts/para_curation.py 2>&1\n\nScript will:\n1. Scan shared project directories\n2. Archive files older than 1 year\n3. Log migration details\n4. Create a migration report\n\nCheck /data/workspace/logs/para_curation.log for details.\n\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774198800000,"lastRunAtMs":1773594000012,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":9737,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","lastDelivered":true},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"}},{"id":"f17da2d2-3b49-4be5-be9d-d29a27a8dbb9","agentId":"main","name":"healthcheck:security-audit","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1770299752473,"updatedAtMs":1773601254716,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 3 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"next-heartbeat","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Run a security audit: execute `openclaw security audit --deep` and `openclaw update status`. Compare results against the last audit. If any NEW findings appear (not previously accepted risks), return them clearly. Save results to memory/security-audit-latest.md. Accepted risks: dangerouslyDisableDeviceAuth=true, Sonnet 4 weak tier warning, Discord allowlist warning.\n\nDo NOT post to any channel; return plain text only. The delivery system handles routing.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":180},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774206000000,"lastRunAtMs":1773601200028,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":54688,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"delivered","lastDelivered":true},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"discord","to":"channel:1468164160398557216"}},{"id":"3db9477e-5dee-4731-bfb4-9e0abfcbcab2","agentId":"main","name":"Weekly Memory Health Check","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1771334751465,"updatedAtMs":1773626420619,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 10 * * 1","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"## Weekly Memory Health Check\n\nRun these checks and report findings:\n\n1. **Index Status**\n   - Run `openclaw memory status` and capture: files indexed, chunks, embeddings cached\n   - If files=0 but embeddings>0: INDEX IS CORRUPTED — run `openclaw memory index --force` to auto-fix, then re-check status\n\n2. **Canary Search Tests**\n   - Search for \"Guillermo\" — should return results\n   - Search for \"TMNT fleet\" — should return results\n   - If both return 0: search is broken\n\n3. **Disk Usage**\n   - Check /data/workspace/memory/ size\n   - Check /data/.openclaw/memory/ size\n\n4. **QMD Status**\n   - Check if any .qmd files exist (should be removed per Feb 23 decision)\n\nReport format:\n- Summary status (PASS/FAIL)\n- Severity (LOW/MEDIUM/HIGH)\n- Any auto-fixes applied\n- Action items if manual intervention needed","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","timeoutSeconds":120},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","to":"channel:1468164160398557216","bestEffort":true},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1774231200000,"lastRunAtMs":1773626400013,"lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":20606,"consecutiveErrors":0,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastDeliveryStatus":"unknown"}},{"id":"9af41e20-e097-474a-ba80-9bb822e4c64d","name":"Monthly Core Files Review","description":"1st of each month: Review SOUL.md/IDENTITY.md accuracy, check MEMORY.md size, update mistake-tracker recurrence counts.","enabled":true,"createdAtMs":1772613275378,"updatedAtMs":1772613275378,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 9 1 * *"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","wakeMode":"now","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Monthly core files review (1st of month, 09:00 HKT).\n\nTasks:\n1. Check MEMORY.md size with wc -c. Must be <5KB. If over, cull immediately.\n2. Review SOUL.md and IDENTITY.md for accuracy.\n3. Check memory/refs/mistake-tracker.md for any recurrences >0.\n4. Post summary to Telegram.\n\nIf all good: MONTHLY_REVIEW_OK\nIf action needed: take it and report.","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5"},"delivery":{"mode":"announce","channel":"last"},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1775005200000}}],"total":19,"offset":0,"limit":19,"hasMore":false,"nextOffset":null},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773880247940}}
{"type":"message","id":"772bf1d0","parentId":"5ab0d7c1","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:15.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to update the nightly memory curation cron job to include PARA vault demotion. The key change is:\n\n1. Update the nightly curation prompt to demote trimmed items to vault/knowledge/\n2. Update AGENTS.md to document this flow\n3. Maybe also update the weekly PARA curation to process demoted items\n\nLet me update the nightly curation cron job first, then document the system.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Found everything. Here's what I'll update:\n\n1. **Nightly curation cron** — add PARA demotion step when trimming MEMORY.md\n2. **AGENTS.md** — document the updated memory flow\n3. **PARA-GUIDE.md** — add demotion protocol\n\nLet me do it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_013knxMD15j8LqVBSeQcBH46","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"update","jobId":"b2d4e6ce-7826-4cd7-b173-2272d7bea43a","patch":{"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","message":"Nightly memory curation — 23:00 HKT. You are in an isolated session.\n\nStep 1 — Read today's daily log and MEMORY.md:\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'No daily log yet'\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\n\nStep 2 — Identify gaps: decisions made today not in MEMORY.md, tasks completed not recorded, lessons learned not captured, infra changes undocumented.\n\nStep 3 — Patch gaps: append any missing durable items to /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md. If MEMORY.md needs updating (new lessons, key decisions), edit it — but keep it under 15KB.\n\nStep 4 — Check MEMORY.md size:\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\nIf over 15000 bytes, you MUST demote before trimming:\n\n**PARA DEMOTION PROTOCOL (mandatory before any trim):**\nFor each item being removed from MEMORY.md:\na) Classify: Is it a Project (has end date)? Area (ongoing)? Resource (reference)? Archive (done/stale)?\nb) Write it to the appropriate vault location:\n   - Active project info → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/projects/{project-name}/\n   - Ongoing area knowledge → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/areas/{area}/\n   - Reference material → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/resources/\n   - Completed/stale → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/archives/\nc) Use descriptive filenames: YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md\nd) Include metadata header: <!-- agent: molty | type: {decision|lesson|status|reference} | priority: {P1|P2|P3} | date: YYYY-MM-DD -->\ne) ONLY AFTER writing to vault, remove from MEMORY.md\n\nNever delete information without demoting it first. Trimming = moving, not deleting.\n\nStep 5 — Archive old daily logs:\nexec: find /data/workspace/memory/ -maxdepth 1 -name '202*.md' -not -name \"$(date +%Y-%m-%d).md\" -not -name \"$(date -d 'yesterday' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-1d +%Y-%m-%d).md\" -mtime +7 -exec mv {} /data/workspace/memory/archive/ \\;\n\nStep 6 — Commit:\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add memory/ MEMORY.md && git commit -m 'memory: nightly curation ${TODAY}' 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\n\nStep 7 — Post summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) using the message tool:\nFormat:\n**🧠 Nightly Memory Curation — {DATE}**\n\n[N gaps found and patched / or: No gaps found — memory current]\n\n**Added:**\n- [item 1]\n- [item 2]\n(or: Nothing to add)\n\n**Demoted to vault:**\n- [item → vault/knowledge/{location}]\n(or: Nothing demoted)\n\n**MEMORY.md:** [size]KB [under/over cap]\n\nDo NOT post if nothing changed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK instead.","timeoutSeconds":300}}}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":1212,"cacheRead":73448,"cacheWrite":13102,"totalTokens":87763,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0303,"cacheRead":0.036724,"cacheWrite":0.0818875,"total":0.1489165}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773880247965}}
{"type":"message","id":"cbf8c8df","parentId":"772bf1d0","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:16.011Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_013knxMD15j8LqVBSeQcBH46","toolName":"cron","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"b2d4e6ce-7826-4cd7-b173-2272d7bea43a\",\n  \"name\": \"Nightly Memory Curation (11PM HKT)\",\n  \"enabled\": true,\n  \"schedule\": {\n    \"kind\": \"cron\",\n    \"expr\": \"0 23 * * *\",\n    \"tz\": \"Asia/Hong_Kong\"\n  },\n  \"sessionTarget\": \"isolated\",\n  \"agentId\": \"\",\n  \"payload\": {\n    \"kind\": \"agentTurn\",\n    \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5\",\n    \"message\": \"Nightly memory curation — 23:00 HKT. You are in an isolated session.\\n\\nStep 1 — Read today's daily log and MEMORY.md:\\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'No daily log yet'\\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\\n\\nStep 2 — Identify gaps: decisions made today not in MEMORY.md, tasks completed not recorded, lessons learned not captured, infra changes undocumented.\\n\\nStep 3 — Patch gaps: append any missing durable items to /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md. If MEMORY.md needs updating (new lessons, key decisions), edit it — but keep it under 15KB.\\n\\nStep 4 — Check MEMORY.md size:\\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\\nIf over 15000 bytes, you MUST demote before trimming:\\n\\n**PARA DEMOTION PROTOCOL (mandatory before any trim):**\\nFor each item being removed from MEMORY.md:\\na) Classify: Is it a Project (has end date)? Area (ongoing)? Resource (reference)? Archive (done/stale)?\\nb) Write it to the appropriate vault location:\\n   - Active project info → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/projects/{project-name}/\\n   - Ongoing area knowledge → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/areas/{area}/\\n   - Reference material → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/resources/\\n   - Completed/stale → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/archives/\\nc) Use descriptive filenames: YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md\\nd) Include metadata header: <!-- agent: molty | type: {decision|lesson|status|reference} | priority: {P1|P2|P3} | date: YYYY-MM-DD -->\\ne) ONLY AFTER writing to vault, remove from MEMORY.md\\n\\nNever delete information without demoting it first. Trimming = moving, not deleting.\\n\\nStep 5 — Archive old daily logs:\\nexec: find /data/workspace/memory/ -maxdepth 1 -name '202*.md' -not -name \\\"$(date +%Y-%m-%d).md\\\" -not -name \\\"$(date -d 'yesterday' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-1d +%Y-%m-%d).md\\\" -mtime +7 -exec mv {} /data/workspace/memory/archive/ \\\\;\\n\\nStep 6 — Commit:\\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add memory/ MEMORY.md && git commit -m 'memory: nightly curation ${TODAY}' 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\\n\\nStep 7 — Post summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) using the message tool:\\nFormat:\\n**🧠 Nightly Memory Curation — {DATE}**\\n\\n[N gaps found and patched / or: No gaps found — memory current]\\n\\n**Added:**\\n- [item 1]\\n- [item 2]\\n(or: Nothing to add)\\n\\n**Demoted to vault:**\\n- [item → vault/knowledge/{location}]\\n(or: Nothing demoted)\\n\\n**MEMORY.md:** [size]KB [under/over cap]\\n\\nDo NOT post if nothing changed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK instead.\",\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 300\n  },\n  \"state\": {\n    \"nextRunAtMs\": 1773932400000,\n    \"lastRunAtMs\": 1773846000009,\n    \"lastRunStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastStatus\": \"ok\",\n    \"lastDurationMs\": 92159,\n    \"lastDeliveryStatus\": \"not-delivered\",\n    \"consecutiveErrors\": 0,\n    \"lastDelivered\": false\n  },\n  \"delivery\": {\n    \"mode\": \"none\"\n  },\n  \"updatedAtMs\": 1773880275975,\n  \"wakeMode\": \"now\"\n}"}],"details":{"id":"b2d4e6ce-7826-4cd7-b173-2272d7bea43a","name":"Nightly Memory Curation (11PM HKT)","enabled":true,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 23 * * *","tz":"Asia/Hong_Kong"},"sessionTarget":"isolated","agentId":"","payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","model":"anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5","message":"Nightly memory curation — 23:00 HKT. You are in an isolated session.\n\nStep 1 — Read today's daily log and MEMORY.md:\nexec: TODAY=$(date +%Y-%m-%d) && cat /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md 2>/dev/null || echo 'No daily log yet'\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\n\nStep 2 — Identify gaps: decisions made today not in MEMORY.md, tasks completed not recorded, lessons learned not captured, infra changes undocumented.\n\nStep 3 — Patch gaps: append any missing durable items to /data/workspace/memory/${TODAY}.md. If MEMORY.md needs updating (new lessons, key decisions), edit it — but keep it under 15KB.\n\nStep 4 — Check MEMORY.md size:\nexec: wc -c /data/workspace/MEMORY.md\nIf over 15000 bytes, you MUST demote before trimming:\n\n**PARA DEMOTION PROTOCOL (mandatory before any trim):**\nFor each item being removed from MEMORY.md:\na) Classify: Is it a Project (has end date)? Area (ongoing)? Resource (reference)? Archive (done/stale)?\nb) Write it to the appropriate vault location:\n   - Active project info → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/projects/{project-name}/\n   - Ongoing area knowledge → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/areas/{area}/\n   - Reference material → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/resources/\n   - Completed/stale → /data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/archives/\nc) Use descriptive filenames: YYYY-MM-DD-{slug}.md\nd) Include metadata header: <!-- agent: molty | type: {decision|lesson|status|reference} | priority: {P1|P2|P3} | date: YYYY-MM-DD -->\ne) ONLY AFTER writing to vault, remove from MEMORY.md\n\nNever delete information without demoting it first. Trimming = moving, not deleting.\n\nStep 5 — Archive old daily logs:\nexec: find /data/workspace/memory/ -maxdepth 1 -name '202*.md' -not -name \"$(date +%Y-%m-%d).md\" -not -name \"$(date -d 'yesterday' +%Y-%m-%d 2>/dev/null || date -v-1d +%Y-%m-%d).md\" -mtime +7 -exec mv {} /data/workspace/memory/archive/ \\;\n\nStep 6 — Commit:\nexec: cd /data/workspace && git add memory/ MEMORY.md && git commit -m 'memory: nightly curation ${TODAY}' 2>/dev/null || echo 'Nothing to commit'\n\nStep 7 — Post summary to Discord #command-center (channel 1468164160398557216) using the message tool:\nFormat:\n**🧠 Nightly Memory Curation — {DATE}**\n\n[N gaps found and patched / or: No gaps found — memory current]\n\n**Added:**\n- [item 1]\n- [item 2]\n(or: Nothing to add)\n\n**Demoted to vault:**\n- [item → vault/knowledge/{location}]\n(or: Nothing demoted)\n\n**MEMORY.md:** [size]KB [under/over cap]\n\nDo NOT post if nothing changed — reply HEARTBEAT_OK instead.","timeoutSeconds":300},"state":{"nextRunAtMs":1773932400000,"lastRunAtMs":1773846000009,"lastRunStatus":"ok","lastStatus":"ok","lastDurationMs":92159,"lastDeliveryStatus":"not-delivered","consecutiveErrors":0,"lastDelivered":false},"delivery":{"mode":"none"},"updatedAtMs":1773880275975,"wakeMode":"now"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773880275980}}
{"type":"message","id":"61ced8a8","parentId":"cbf8c8df","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:19.411Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update AGENTS.md with the memory flow:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_011hvomQ9c2WVb3kmsJMYqse","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"/data/workspace/AGENTS.md","offset":1,"limit":20}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":107,"cacheRead":86550,"cacheWrite":2487,"totalTokens":89145,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.0026750000000000003,"cacheRead":0.043275,"cacheWrite":0.01554375,"total":0.061498750000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773880276010}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff335928","parentId":"61ced8a8","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:19.471Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_011hvomQ9c2WVb3kmsJMYqse","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# AGENTS.md - Your Workspace\n\n## Every Session\n1. Read `SOUL.md` — who you are\n2. Read `USER.md` — who you're helping\n3. Read `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (today + yesterday)\n4. **Main session only:** Read `MEMORY.md`\n5. **Main session only:** Read `TODO.md` — my active task list\n6. Read `PRIORITY_BRIEFING.md` — surface priorities FIRST when Guillermo messages\n7. Check `REGRESSIONS.md` — hard rules from past failures. Do not repeat them.\n\n## Before Any Calendar Operation\n- Use SA token ONLY: `google-service-account.json` + no delegation. See `memory/refs/standup-process.md`.\n- Do NOT use `calendar-tokens-brinc.json` — it expires and can't be refreshed headlessly.\n- Brinc busy block is now AUTOMATIC in cal_create — no flag needed.\n- Check all 3 calendars for conflicts before booking.\n\n## Before Any MC API Call\n- GET = `/api/tasks` (plural). POST/PATCH = `/api/task` (singular).\n- Wrong endpoint = silent failure. Double-check before executing.\n\n[182 more lines in file. Use offset=21 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1773880279443}}
{"type":"message","id":"d04c6101","parentId":"ff335928","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:30.974Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01S4LXqTZYxgCkGMPvXSXcwD","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/data/workspace/AGENTS.md","old_string":"## Memory\n- **Daily:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — raw logs\n- **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — curated, under 15KB\n- **Always search MEMORY.md** before answering about infrastructure, credentials, prior decisions, people, or project state\n- **Write it down** — \"mental notes\" don't survive restarts","new_string":"## Memory Architecture\n**5-layer system — nothing gets deleted, only demoted:**\n\n| Layer | File/Path | Loaded at startup? | Reliability |\n|-------|-----------|-------------------|-------------|\n| 1. Regressions | `REGRESSIONS.md` | ✅ Always | 🟢 Highest |\n| 2. Working memory | `MEMORY.md` (≤15KB) | ✅ Always | 🟢 High |\n| 3. Reference docs | `memory/refs/` | ❌ Search only | 🟡 Medium |\n| 4. PARA Vault | `memory/vault/knowledge/` | ❌ Search only | 🟡 Medium |\n| 5. Daily logs | `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` → `archive/` | ✅ Today+yesterday | 🔴 Degrades |\n\n**The rule: Trimming = moving, not deleting.**\nWhen MEMORY.md exceeds 15KB, demote items to the PARA vault before removing:\n- Projects (end date) → `vault/knowledge/projects/{name}/`\n- Areas (ongoing) → `vault/knowledge/areas/{area}/`\n- Resources (reference) → `vault/knowledge/resources/`\n- Done/stale → `vault/knowledge/archives/`\n\n**Always search MEMORY.md + vault** before answering about infrastructure, credentials, prior decisions, people, or project state.\n**Write it down** — \"mental notes\" don't survive restarts."}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":547,"cacheRead":89037,"cacheWrite":428,"totalTokens":90013,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.013675000000000001,"cacheRead":0.044518499999999996,"cacheWrite":0.0026750000000000003,"total":0.0608735}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773880279470}}
{"type":"message","id":"edc7b6f0","parentId":"d04c6101","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:31.034Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"toolu_01S4LXqTZYxgCkGMPvXSXcwD","toolName":"edit","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully replaced text in /data/workspace/AGENTS.md."}],"details":{"diff":"     ...\n  45 ## Before Any External Send (email, webhook, message)\n  46 - Is this Guillermo's voice or Molty's? Don't conflate.\n  47 - Draft first, confirm before sending for anything non-routine.\n  48 \n- 49 ## Memory\n- 50 - **Daily:** `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` — raw logs\n- 51 - **Long-term:** `MEMORY.md` — curated, under 15KB\n- 52 - **Always search MEMORY.md** before answering about infrastructure, credentials, prior decisions, people, or project state\n- 53 - **Write it down** — \"mental notes\" don't survive restarts\n+ 49 ## Memory Architecture\n+ 50 **5-layer system — nothing gets deleted, only demoted:**\n  54 \n+ 52 | Layer | File/Path | Loaded at startup? | Reliability |\n+ 53 |-------|-----------|-------------------|-------------|\n+ 54 | 1. Regressions | `REGRESSIONS.md` | ✅ Always | 🟢 Highest |\n+ 55 | 2. Working memory | `MEMORY.md` (≤15KB) | ✅ Always | 🟢 High |\n+ 56 | 3. Reference docs | `memory/refs/` | ❌ Search only | 🟡 Medium |\n+ 57 | 4. PARA Vault | `memory/vault/knowledge/` | ❌ Search only | 🟡 Medium |\n+ 58 | 5. Daily logs | `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` → `archive/` | ✅ Today+yesterday | 🔴 Degrades |\n+ 59 \n+ 60 **The rule: Trimming = moving, not deleting.**\n+ 61 When MEMORY.md exceeds 15KB, demote items to the PARA vault before removing:\n+ 62 - Projects (end date) → `vault/knowledge/projects/{name}/`\n+ 63 - Areas (ongoing) → `vault/knowledge/areas/{area}/`\n+ 64 - Resources (reference) → `vault/knowledge/resources/`\n+ 65 - Done/stale → `vault/knowledge/archives/`\n+ 66 \n+ 67 **Always search MEMORY.md + vault** before answering about infrastructure, credentials, prior decisions, people, or project state.\n+ 68 **Write it down** — \"mental notes\" don't survive restarts.\n+ 69 \n  55 ## Safety\n  56 - Don't exfiltrate private data\n  57 - `trash` > `rm`\n  58 - Ask before destructive/external actions\n     ...","firstChangedLine":49},"isError":false,"timestamp":1773880291005}}
{"type":"message","id":"a3072531","parentId":"edc7b6f0","timestamp":"2026-03-19T00:31:38.453Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now update the PARA guide:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_017pj6dW7dfuoMijLqiyy2du","name":"edit","arguments":{"file_path":"/data/workspace/memory/vault/knowledge/PARA-GUIDE.md","old_string":"### 2. Molty Curates (Weekly)\n\nEvery week, Molty:\n- Reviews flagged learnings from all team leads\n- Migrates insights to appropriate PARA locations\n- Cross-pollinates: shares relevant learnings across agents\n- Archives completed project milestones","new_string":"### 2. Molty Curates (Nightly + Weekly)\n\n**Nightly (23:00 HKT) — PARA Demotion:**\nWhen MEMORY.md exceeds 15KB, items are demoted here before removal:\n- Classify each item: Project / Area / Resource / Archive\n- Write to appropriate vault path with metadata header\n- Only remove from MEMORY.md after vault write confirms\n\n**Weekly (Monday 01:00 HKT) — Deep Curation:**\n- Reviews flagged learnings from all team leads\n- Migrates insights to appropriate PARA locations\n- Cross-pollinates: shares relevant learnings across agents\n- Archives completed project milestones"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-opus-4-6","usage":{"input":1,"output":339,"cacheRead":89465,"cacheWrite":572,"totalTokens":90377,"cost":{"input":0.000005,"output":0.008475,"cacheRead":0.0447325,"cacheWrite":0.003575,"total":0.056787500000000005}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1773880291033}}
